This paper deals with the impact of spectrum allocation on the coverage probability of picocells in the context of intercell interference coordination (ICIC) with macro base stations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analytical expressions and optimization techniques, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of frequency allocation on the average rate, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves coordination between different base stations, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with wireless communication, which could place it in cs.COM (Computers and Society).
